INSERT INTO `products` (`id`, `category_id`, `sub_category_id`, `product_name`, `description`, `status`, `date_created`) VALUES
(1, 1, 1, 'Ella', 'Little Ella is looking for her forever home.\n\nElla is a sweet girl with a lot of energy. She hasn\'t had any of the puppy training or socialisation that every puppy needs, so she will need some ongoing training to ensure she grows into her best pup self.\n\nShe hasn\'t quite mastered her impulse control and she gets so excited when she sees hoomans that she can\'t help herself and can get a bit jumpy. She\'s also not ben taught just how good cuddles can be so she\'ll need lots of love while she gets up to speed. Because of these she will need to go to a home with older teenage children or adults only.\n\nShe\'s not really sure how she\'s supposed to walk on lead, is it this way? That way? Am I supposed to jump? Who Knows! So she will need to go home with a balance harness and lead.\n\nElla has also never been around other dogs so has no idea what to do when she sees another pooch. She will need to be introduced slowly to ensure she has positive experiences with other dogs and learns to get along with them well.', 1, '2021-06-21 11:19:31'),
(2, 1, 1, 'Randal', 'Hi! I\'m Randall!\n\nThe humans in the LDH tell me everyday that I\'m the coolest and prettiest boy in the shelter, though I don\'t let it get to my head. I\'m really a humble dude with the occasional burst of energy.\n\nI\'ve made loads of friends in the shelter, mainly with humans, but more recently a few dogs that don\'t get up in my face. While it\'s pretty sociable here, I\'m keen to get out. Just imagine, we could be relaxing together in your home!\n\nIt would be awesome to live with a few adult humans or maybe a few level headed kids. My preference is to be the only dog in the the house, so I can get all the play-time, pats, walks and treats.\n\nI reckon a more quite vibe would suit, as I can be startled by loud noises and unexpected activity. My trainer in here has taught me to check when on walks, I love learning new stuff and might even shake your hand when you come in to say hi!\n\nI\'m also learning that being independent is actually pretty cool. Saying that, I\'m definitely more a fan of hanging-out, so would prefer someone who is home most of the time. Almost forgot, I do have a history of going on a few solo adventures, so make sure there is secure fencing in the yard.', 1, '2021-06-21 16:48:16'),
(3, 1, 1, 'Crayon', 'Arriving at the shelter through no fault of his own Crayon was initially very scared & worried but after a few weeks of TLC and bonding with staff members he is now ready to find his new forever home.\n\nCrayon is a sweet boy who as mentioned is a little timid at first, he needs his new adopters to take it slow with him & give him his space, once he finds his confidence he\'s a playful boy who loves toys & zoomies! He\'s also very treat motivated which is great for building a bond & doing on going training!\n\nCrayon would prefer to go to a calm adults only household where he\'ll be given space & time to settle & eventually flourish!\n\nHe\'d also prefer to be the only dog in the household. He has shown some nice social skills with other dogs but generally prefers to keep himself to himself.', 1, '2021-06-21 16:49:07'),
(4, 1, 1, 'Lucy Jordan', 'Hi, I am Lucy Jordan!\n\nIt has been said that I would like to \"RIDE THROUGH PARIS, IN A SPORTS CAR, WITH THE WARM WIND IN MY HAIR\";\nbut i would prefer to find my perfect forever home. Could this be you?\n\nI am a sweet, easy going gal, who is looking for a family home where I can flourish and become the amazing dog, I know I am.\n\nI really don\'t like being left alone much, so I would prefer it if my new family are able to spend lots of time with me and continue to help me feel safe when you are absent. I really like to be kept busy so providing me with a variety enrichment will help. Food dispensing toys, chews, kongs and toys are my jam!\n\nI would need to be the only dog in the home for now. Most dogs can be too fast and keen to say hello and they can make me feel a little uneasy. I can come across quite rude if I am forced to interact.', 1, '2021-06-21 16:50:11'),
(5, 1, 2, 'Mali', 'Meet Mali, our sweetheart with the love heart nose <3\n\nMali is quite shy and can be a little conflicted at times. She loves humans, but can still be a little wary. You will notice her careful approach when you meet her - but once you start showing her some affection with pats, she knows she is loved.\n\nIt won\'t be long before she is purring and smooching you right back!\n\nMali is startled easily by loud noises, so a quiet home with adults only or a family including secondary aged children would be best suited.', 1, '2021-06-22 15:50:16'),
(6, 1, 2, 'Tinker', 'Attention all humans! Are you looking for a gentle, kind-hearted kitty to cuddle all your worries away??\n\nWell look no further because Tiny Tinker needs you!\n\nTinker is a sweet girl who enjoys gentle pats and gives gentle little smooches. She would like her home to have a slow approach with her, until she becomes comfortable. We promise she has a lot of love to give, she just needs to feel safe and comofortable <3\n\nShe is great at making biscuits and loves kneading her blanket almost instantly when you start patting her. We think she will be the ultimate purr machine in no time!', 1, '2022-08-06 20:42:03'),
(7, 1, 2, 'Skye', 'Skye is a smoochy girl, but once she has had enough, she will definitely let you know - usually with a bit of a warning swipe. For this reason, we are looking for an adult only home that can respect her boundaries.\n', 1, '2022-08-06 20:42:03'),
(8, 1, 2, 'SnoopySmudge', 'A very shy boy who was quite shut down when he came into our care. It\'s taken a lot of TLC to allow snoopy to come out of his shell and he\'s now looking for a quite place to call home.\n\nDon\'t let his timid nature fool you, he\'s quite smoochy once he\'s out of his shell.\n\nDue to his shy nature, Snoopy will need a quite home with adults only and A LOT of patience as little hoomans may be a little too much for him. His new hoomans will need to understand that it\'ll take a while before his affectionate personality shows.\n\nSnoopy has lived with other feline friends, but he tells us that they cramped his style. Therefore he will need to be the only other fur-friend in his new home.', 1, '2022-08-06 20:48:46'),
(9, 1, 1, 'Casey', 'A sweet but shy girl looking for a quite home to claim her place on her hoomans couch.\n\nShe can be shy at first but good chin scratch tends to win her over.\n\nChildren may be a little too much for her so older kids who understand she may want time to herself would be best.\n\nCasey is Feline Immunodeficiency Virus (FIV+) so she will need to be an indoor only kitty. She may be open to sharing her spot on the couch with a feline pal who is also FIV+.', 1, '2022-08-06 20:48:46'),
(10, 1, 2, 'Reginald', 'You could be mistaken for thinking that Reginald is angry in his photo however he is simply trying his best to get the treats out of my hand and into his mouth!\n\nReginald was surrendered to the shelter with his sister Mollee and was very shy when he came in. In fact his first photo was taken with him hiding under his blanket, terrified by everything. Now this beautiful man is happy and outgoing and is the first out of his pen to explore the adoption rooms.\n\nReggie and Mollee love each other and it would be lovely for them to find a home together, they are always found cuddled up together sleeping or eating. They are littermates and as such have always been together.\n', 1, '2022-08-06 20:50:17'),
(11, 1, 2, 'Olive', 'Olive is a cutie pie who loves to come over for a quick chin scratch before she\'s off again.\n\nShe tends to keep to herself so a quite home with older kids who understand she may want space would be best for her.\n\nShe\'s quite shy but treats will win her over ;)', 1, '2022-08-06 20:50:17'),
(14, 1, 2, 'Popcorn', '&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: inherit; border: 0px; outline: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 0em; margin-bottom: 1.55em; color: rgb(124, 123, 123); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Meet Popcorn, a tame female cat with beautiful calico colouring. She&rsquo;s about 3+ years old sterilized. An independent lady, Popcorn loves delicious soft food and naps in her favourite spots &ndash; the quiet life.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: inherit; border: 0px; outline: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 0em; margin-bottom: 1.55em; color: rgb(124, 123, 123); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Popcorn was spotted wandering in the estate, hungry and uncertain. We found out that she used to be a house cat. Her previous owner had given her up and she and had been wandering for a long while.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2022-08-07 15:21:18'),
(15, 1, 2, 'Buddy', '&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: inherit; border: 0px; outline: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 0em; margin-bottom: 1.55em; color: rgb(124, 123, 123); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Meet Buddy, a charming and wonderfully loving male cat. He is about 2 years old sterilized. He loves to explore his surroundings. He would do wonderfully in a home as an only cat. FIV FeLV negative.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: inherit; border: 0px; outline: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 0em; margin-bottom: 1.55em; color: rgb(124, 123, 123); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;This sweetie was heartlessly abandoned at the void deck of one housing block some weeks ago and rescued.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: inherit; border: 0px; outline: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 0em; margin-bottom: 1.55em; color: rgb(124, 123, 123); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;If you would like to meet Buddy, willing to cat-proof the home and offer good quality of good quality soft and dry food, please contact us&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2022-08-08 07:07:11'),
(16, 1, 2, 'Bui Bui (aka Chubby)', '&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: inherit; border: 0px; outline: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 0em; margin-bottom: 1.55em; color: rgb(124, 123, 123); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Bui Bui (aka Chubby) is a lovely Siamese cross, 1+ year old female sterilized. She&rsquo;s a little shy with new people but when she gets to know you, you will see that she has a huge heart and lots of love to give. She likes to hang out with the people she trusts and follow them around. FIV FeLV negative.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: inherit; border: 0px; outline: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 0em; margin-bottom: 1.55em; color: rgb(124, 123, 123); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;This sweetie came from a very difficult hoarding situation where the house was overcrowded.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2022-08-08 07:14:28'),
(17, 1, 2, 'Mila', '&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: inherit; border: 0px; outline: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 0em; margin-bottom: 1.55em; color: rgb(124, 123, 123); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Meet Mila, a pretty 10-month old tabby cat, female sterilized. A sweet and cute little gal who was rescued from a migrant workers&rsquo; dormitory. She&rsquo;s happy to be rescued and safe.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: inherit; border: 0px; outline: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 0em; margin-bottom: 1.55em; color: rgb(124, 123, 123); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Despite her tiny size, Mila is quite adventurous and loves to run around. She&rsquo;s interested in the world around her. She is easy-going with a good all-round nature.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2022-08-08 07:16:02'),
(18, 1, 2, 'Cream', '&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: inherit; border: 0px; outline: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 0em; margin-bottom: 1.55em; color: rgb(124, 123, 123); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Introducing Cream, about 3 years old male sterilized. This handsome fellow has a quiet and good all-round nature. When given a soft cushion, he will spend time kneading away. He&rsquo;s a great choice for first time cat owner.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: inherit; border: 0px; outline: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-top: 0em; margin-bottom: 1.55em; color: rgb(124, 123, 123); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Cream was given up by his previous family who could no longer able to care for him. He is a medium/long haired cat and will require regular brushing/grooming.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2022-08-08 07:20:44'),
(19, 1, 1, 'Dale', '&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &amp;quot;Open Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Dale is a sweet and sensitive 10 year old collie boy. He&#039;s a quiet boy who is looking forward to starting the next chapter in his life. He can initially be quite shy and needs a little time to build his confidence. Once he&#039;s comfortable he loves a gentle stroll where he can explore all the sniffs.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &amp;quot;Open Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Dale is looking for a calm and patient home where he can take life at his own pace. He&#039;d need any time alone to be built up slowly once he&#039;s settled in. He may be able to live with another dog providing they get along here at the centre. He&#039;ll be suitable to live with children aged 14 and above who are used to dogs. Dale is looking to have a quiet retirement home where he can grow old with grace and enjoy his golden years.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2022-08-08 07:23:42'),
(20, 1, 1, 'Dot', '&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &amp;quot;Open Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Dot is a gorgeous 3 year old Spitz cross who is looking for a calm and quiet, female only home with no visiting children. She is worried by other dogs so will need to be the only dog in the home and further socialization will be beneficial once she&#039;s settled and gained more confidence.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &amp;quot;Open Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Dot is a timid girl who has not had a great start in life. She will need patient owners willing to go at her pace in building up her confidence. She is very foody so this will help with training once she&#039;s settled. Dot would prefer quieter walks away from lots of hustle and bustle. She would love her own secure garden with direct access from the home.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &amp;quot;Open Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Dot has been unsure around males so is looking for a female only home. Potential owners must be able to come and visit Dot at least 3 times before she goes home. If you are shortlisted for this dog please be aware a meet will be arranged at the centre within 48 hours and your new family member may be home with you within 7 days.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2022-08-08 07:24:48'),
(21, 1, 1, 'SHIRO', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(75, 85, 99); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: medium; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Shiro likes to play with toys, and is very smart. He is a moderately high drive dog like most herding breeds and likes activity on his terms. He likes his walks but his insecurities keep him from being a dog park dog. He bonds heavily with a particular person and sometimes a particular dog - he is IN LOVE with the dog SNOW KITTY at the Milo Sanctuary, and would follow him anywhere. Shiro is wary of strangers but is very loyal to his people and for this reason he can be protective. He needs a very predictable, low stim. home to be successful. Training and building Shiro&#039;s confidence would be key to have Shiro flourish.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2022-08-08 07:26:30'),
(22, 1, 1, 'Milly', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(75, 85, 99); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: medium; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Milly is a gorgeous and loving dog with those she knows. She is long, lanky and elegant! She&#039;s completed puppy manners training, knows many basic commands and is housebroken. She loves to catch biscuits and play chase with dog friends, stretching her long legs - she is beautiful in motion! Milly is energetic, so outdoor space to explore and run around is a must, and she loves a nice dog bed or couch (if allowed) to lounge on!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); color: rgb(75, 85, 99); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: medium; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); color: rgb(75, 85, 99); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: medium; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(75, 85, 99); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: medium; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Milly is playful and social with male dogs and usually fine with non dominating females. She is better off leash than on, so introductions where leashes can be dropped after a short walk side by side is best practice.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); color: rgb(75, 85, 99); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: medium; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); color: rgb(75, 85, 99); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: medium; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(75, 85, 99); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: medium; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Milly is a sweet big, girl waiting for her forever home. She would love to have a male dog companion to run and play with, she deserves a spacious area and a home life with understanding people. An adult-only home with Guardian Breed experience would be ideal, preferably with some land for her to roam, and protect. Milly will do well with someone who understands resource guarding and is comfortable and experienced with training. Milly is such a regal beauty, she can be silly as well as serious, she is not a first-time dog. She has a lot of joy in her, and has a lot of love to give.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2022-08-08 07:30:40'),
(23, 1, 7, 'JULIP', '&lt;div class=&quot;field field-tax-ref-location inline&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(99, 100, 102); font-family: &amp;quot;Open Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: 0.48px; word-spacing: -0.2px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot; style=&quot;display: inline;&quot;&gt;Location&lt;/div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;div class=&quot;field-content&quot; style=&quot;display: inline; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(61, 61, 62);&quot;&gt;Sanctuary (Kanab)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-animal-breed inline&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(99, 100, 102); font-family: &amp;quot;Open Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: 0.48px; word-spacing: -0.2px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot; style=&quot;display: inline;&quot;&gt;Looks like&lt;/div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;div class=&quot;field-content&quot; style=&quot;display: inline; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(61, 61, 62);&quot;&gt;Parakeet - Other&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-animal-color inline&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(99, 100, 102); font-family: &amp;quot;Open Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: 0.48px; word-spacing: -0.2px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot; style=&quot;display: inline;&quot;&gt;Color&lt;/div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;div class=&quot;field-content&quot; style=&quot;display: inline; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(61, 61, 62);&quot;&gt;Green&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-animal-sex inline&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(99, 100, 102); font-family: &amp;quot;Open Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: 0.48px; word-spacing: -0.2px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot; style=&quot;display: inline;&quot;&gt;Sex&lt;/div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;div class=&quot;field-content&quot; style=&quot;display: inline; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(61, 61, 62);&quot;&gt;Female&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(99, 100, 102); font-family: &amp;quot;Open Sans&amp;quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; letter-spacing: 0.48px; word-spacing: -0.2px;&quot;&gt;Julip is a budgie, or budgerigar, who is looking for her new forever home. She prefers the company of other birds, so she would do best in an aviary situation or in a patient home that is willing to work her and a buddy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2022-08-08 07:33:32'),
